title: Olivia Chien’s CV
text:
Accounting Major Student.

Olivia Linkedin Page 




Mandarin (Native), English (Fluent)
Communication Skills.
Computer Skills: Microsoft.
Multiple Tasks




Apr 2023 - Now Peer Advisor (Idaho- BYU-I)

Consulted 30+ campus students per week to demonstrate communication skills and fluency in English
Conduct weekly advisor training with other advisors to improve public speaking and teamwork experience
Finish team’s project daily by using MS Office and Excel

Jan 2023 - Apr 2023 Custodian (Idaho- BYU-I)

Trained newly hired employees on daily tasks and built good relationships
Coordinated fellows to finish daily assignments in a timely and professional mannans

June 2022 - Aug 2022 Waitress (Taiwan- McDonald’s)

Promoted new products and ordered meals to customers daily to enhance customer service skills
Prepared (including meals, drinks, snacks, etc.), packaged, and delivered food for customs within 2 minutes to show multiple tasks and teamwork ability

May 2021 - Aug 2021 Tutor (Taiwan)

Prepared 3+ lessons per week and practiced questions for first-grade students
Communicated and reported daily to parents about student’s academic progress




Oct 2019 - Apr 2021 Missionary (Taiwan - Missionary–The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints)

Taught 15+ people per week with another assigned missionary to strengthen teamwork and teaching ability
Training new missionaries to communicate with people and daily missionary schedules
Conducted monthly meetings and created training materials for missionaries




2016-2019 Foreign High School.
Sep 2022 - now Brigham Young University–Idaho
